body_html:
I'm having issues with the one_shot_iterator from a Dataset when using in a monitoredTrainingSession on Google cloudML. Issue is that the dataset is iterated through multiple times when running on multiple workers. Also, tensorboard complains:

WARNING:tensorflow:Found more than one graph event per run, or there was a metagraph containing a graph_def, as well as one or more graph events. Overwriting the graph with the newest event.

I'm guessing a similar registration method as provided by @gmichaeljaison might solve this issue for single_shot_iterator as well. However, Iterator has no string_handle method in tf 1.2 (the latest and greatest Google cloud ML version).

Any hints how to make @gmichaeljaison solution work on tf 1.2?

body:
I'm having issues with the one_shot_iterator from a Dataset when using in a monitoredTrainingSession on Google cloudML. Issue is that the dataset is iterated through multiple times when running on multiple workers. Also, tensorboard complains:

> WARNING:tensorflow:Found more than one graph event per run, or there was a metagraph containing a graph_def, as well as one or more graph events.  Overwriting the graph with the newest event.

I'm guessing a similar registration method as provided by @gmichaeljaison might solve this issue for single_shot_iterator as well. However, Iterator has no string_handle method in tf 1.2 (the latest and greatest Google cloud ML version).

Any hints how to make @gmichaeljaison solution work on tf 1.2?
